The paper discusses the application of negative selection approach in network security, specifically in intrusion detection systems. This falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also mentions the use of artificial immune systems, which is a subfield of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The algorithms used in negative selection approach involve machine learning techniques, which can be categorized under machine learning (cs.LG) and neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper discusses the challenges and recommendations for future work, which can be categorized under social and information networks (cs.SI).
